dataIdInfo.idAbs: Runs a weighted threat model based on habitats and threats.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Produced at NCEAS by Shaun Walbridge based on work by Matthew Perry, Carrie Kappel and Ben Halpern.

tool.name: ThreatModel

param.name: Habitats_Folder
param.dialogReference: Presence-Absence habit layers (0 or 1) should be placed in this folder, with names which match the first row of the matrix file used.

param.name: Threats_Folder
param.dialogReference: Natural log and normalized (0-1) threat layers should be placed in this folder, with names which match the first column of the matrix file used.

param.name: Matrix_CSV
param.dialogReference: A CSV which contains threat-matrix interaction values.

param.name: Output_Folder
param.dialogReference: Folder which will contain model outputs, including the final model result and other combination footprint layers.

param.name: By Threat
param.dialogReference: Calculate impacts from individual threats on all habitats.

param.name: By Habitat
param.dialogReference: Calculate impacts from all threats on individual habitats.

param.name: Average Num Habitats
param.displayname: Average impacts by number of habitats
param.dialogReference: Average impacts from individual threats by number of habitats present in each pixel. Resulting cumulative model output will also have pixels averaged by number of habitats. (Note: this option does not apply to 'by_habitats' calculations of impacts on individual habitats.)

param.name: Set Null Zero
param.dialogReference: Replace null values in input rasters with zeros. If not checked then a null value present in a single layer will lead to null values present in resulting model rasters.

tool.summary: Runs a weighted threat model based on habitats and threats.
tool.usage: The matrix file referenced should contain one column per habitat, and one row per threat, with all names matching the rasters to be used in the analysis.
